Titolo: Darxide

Anno: 1996

Descrizione: Darxide (stylized as DarXide) is a shoot 'em up for the 32X by Frontier Developments, released in January 1996 only in Europe.  Designed by David Braben, it was one of the last releases for the 32X console. Gameplay is similar to that of Asteroids in three dimensions. Players must destroy a number of space rocks in order to complete each level.
Reception of Darxide is mixed. The game was followed in 2004 by Darxide EMP, an expanded version released for Pocket PCs and Nokia mobile phones.

Genere: Shoot \'em up

Valutazione: N/A
